LEX The Proposer.

"First Person" is a person.
"Mage" is a person.
"Gap" is a person.
"Lever Plan" is a text.
"Killed Levers Cited" is a binary.

The First Person appoints the Mage, and appoints the Gap.

CLAUSE: Cite.
The Mage may declare Killed Levers Cited.

CLAUSE: Propose.
The Mage may, if Killed Levers Cited is declared: send the Lever Plan to the Gap.
